  "time_ut": 1656662276,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dd9\u0ddf\u0d9b\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dba \u0db8\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dbd \u0d85\u0daf\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Health workers are still in queues today",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "To provide fuel to the staff including doctors of hospitals and health institutions, it was done today (1) at 92 gas stations across the country, and it was reported that many hospital activities were disrupted due to the health staff waiting in long queues since last night (30) to get fuel from them.",
        "Dr. Haritha Aluthge, Secretary to the Government Medical Officers' Association (GMOA) said that hospital staff, including doctors, had to wait in queues for hours to get fuel and had no other date to manage their treatment.",
        "Mr. Aluthge said that due to this, the activities of the outpatient treatment units of many hospitals, including the Gampaha Basic Hospital, had been disrupted.",
        "The doctor mentioned that problems arose during the dispensing of fuel from the filling stations of Galle Fort, Akkareipattu, Navainna and Matara Maddawatta, which were reserved for the health staff, as the general public also came and asked for fuel.",
        "He said that the army and the police intervened and clarified the matter to the people and provided an opportunity for the health staff to get fuel.",
        "Mr. Aluthge also said that some of the Ceypetco filling stations which were reserved for the distribution of fuel to the health staff had not received fuel till this afternoon (1) and the health staff had been waiting in queues due to this.",
        "Also, the Governor of the Western Province had taken action to obtain fuel for the waste transport vehicles from the filling stations allocated to the health staff in Gampaha district, and as a result of this, he requested the Petroleum Corporation to send more fuel bowsers to the health staff as there may not be enough fuel to supply them. said the doctor.",
        "He also said that a program should be prepared next week for the health staff to get fuel without having to wait in queues.",
        "Mr. Haritha Aluthge also said that the people should understand that if the hospital system collapses due to lack of fuel for the health staff and hospitals, they will be affected and their lives will be at risk.",
        "He also stated that out of 1,300 gas stations across the country, only 92 gas stations reserve only one day a week to provide fuel to health workers.",
        "Eighty-four petrol stations were set aside for health staff last Friday, but many hospitals were disrupted due to a shortage of fuel on that day as well."
      ],
